snippet: Engineers in charge of a $3.1 billion tunnel project say that 30 or more nearby buildings have unexpectedly settled.
abstract: Seattle is constructing one of nation's largest highway tunnels, project that has been plagued by series of setbacks, and city now faces new and possibly game-changing discovery; project engineers report that 30 or more buildings in historic Pioneer Square area have unexpectedly settled, with residents reporting cracked walls; City Council members are pressing for clear answers over whether project now poses safety hazard.
lead_paragraph: Engineers in charge of a $3.1 billion tunnel project say that 30 or more nearby buildings have unexpectedly settled.

headline.main: In Seattle, a Sinking Feeling About a Troubled Tunnel
headline.print_headline: In Seattle, Sinking Feeling About Tunnel
